    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "source": [
        "The plot \"X and Y Over Time\" revealed that both Public Concern for Crime (Y) and the Homicide Rate (X) exhibit a clear downward trend, followed by a bounce back at the end of the period.  This sort of pattern indicates that the annual series may be non-stationary (their statistical properties change over time).  Though their co-movement suggests that they may relate to each other."
